<H3> <TI>   Heilongjiang Governor Resigns, Acting Governor Named </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Heilongjiang Governor Resigns, Acting Governor Named </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2105104494 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0820 
GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2105104494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Wang Laixi (3769 0171 0823)] </F>
  [Text] Harbin, 21 May (XINHUA) -- The ninth session of 
the Eighth Heilongjiang Provincial People's Congress Standing 
Committee on 21 May appointed Tian Fengshan [deputy secretary of 
the provincial party committee] vice governor and acting 
governor of the provincial people's government. Tian was 
nominated for the post by the chairmanship meeting of the eighth 
provincial people's congress standing committee. At the same 
time, the ninth session approved Shao Qihui's resignation from 
the post of governor of the provincial people's government. 

</TEXT>

