<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Taipei, Guatemala City Sign Vocational Training Pact </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Taipei, Guatemala City Sign Vocational Training Pact </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2405092894 Taipei CNA in English 0738 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2405092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Danielle Yang] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, May 24 (CNA) -- The Republic of China [ROC] 
and Guatemala signed a vocational training technical cooperation 
agreement Tuesday [24 May] to strengthen bilateral vocational 
training between the two countries. 
  Chairman of Council of Labor Affairs Chao Shou-po and 
Guatemalan Labor Affairs Minister Gladys Anabela Morfin Mancilla 
signed the agreement in Taipei on behalf of their two 
governments. 
  The agreement is the first vocational training agreement the 
ROC has signed with a foreign country, Chao said. 
  Since June 1992, the ROC Government has assisted Guatemala 
in 
setting up vocational training centers in the Central American 
country, Chao said. He added that the centers have trained many 
technical experts during the past two years. 
  Taiwan has promoted overseas vocational training technical 
cooperation programs since 1990 and is assisting in the training 
of technical manpower to upgrade the industrial level of 
friendly developing countries, Chao said. 
  Over the past three years, a total of 30 foreign countries 
have sent 257 personnel to the island for training and the 
government has established vocational training centers in the 
Philippines, Costa Rica, and Guatemala. 

</TEXT>

