<H3> <TI>   Plans for Launching Foreign Satellites To Proceed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Plans for Launching Foreign Satellites To Proceed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2405090594 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0718 
GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2405090594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 24 May (XINHUA) -- According to the China 
Satellite Launch Tracking and Control Department: The accident 
of the meteorological satellite, the "Fengyun II," will not 
affect China's plan of launching satellites for foreign 
countries. Chinese authorities, after consulting with the 
Hughes Aircraft Corporation of the United States, have decided 
to proceed with the original plans of launching the three 
foreign satellites -- the "Asiasat I," the "Asiasat II," and the 
"Optus B3" -- during the second half of the year. 

</TEXT>

